# <li>A widely used, exact simulation method for continuous time Markov chains is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gillespie_algorithm">Gillspie‚Äôs algorithm</a> <span class="citation">(Gillespie 1977)</span>. We do not put much emphasis on Gillespie‚Äôs algorithm here. Why? When would you prefer an implementation of Gillespie‚Äôs algorithm to an Euler solution?</li>
